==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''[[sin]]''
===Noun===
'''Sinn''' ''m''

# [[sense]], [[meaning]]
# [[point]], [[idea]], [[tenor]]
# [[mind]], [[consciousness]]
# [[feeling]]
# (''med'') [[sense]], [[sensus]], [[aesthesia]] (''Brit'')/[[esthesia]] (''Am'')

===Related terms===
*[[Sensus]]
*[[sinnen]]
*[[sinnig]]
*[[sinlich]]
*[[sinnlos]]
*[[sinnvoll]]

===Compounds===
*[[Sinngebung]]
*[[Sinnesnerv]]
*[[Sinnestäuschung]]
*[[Sinneswahrnehmung]]

===Usage===
* ''Sinn haben'', ''Sinn ergeben'' &rarr; ''to make sense''
* ''im Sinn haben'' &rarr; ''to have in mind''
* ''in den Sinn kommen'' &rarr; ''to cross so.'s mind''
* ''in jedem Sinn'' &rarr; ''in every sense''
* ''der Sinn und Zweck'' &rarr; ''the whole purpose''
* ''lange Rede kurzer Sinn'' &rarr; ''to cut a long story short''
* ''ohne Sinn und Verstand'' &rarr; ''nonsensically''
* ''Aus den Augen, aus dem Sinn'' &rarr; ''Out of sight, out of mind''

